  "description": "<i>Magic Spells</i> is an early educational program for multiple systems.<br><br>Designed to teach children age 6 - 10 basic spelling and grammar rules, in consists of a a series of three mini-games with animated graphics and sound.  In each section, the player can choose words from a number of categories, including: animals, orchestra, fruit, and more.<br><br><i>Scramble Spells</i> - The player is given a list of words, and the letters have been scrambled.  The player must correctly unscramble each word.<br><br><i>Flash Spells</i> - Words are displayed on the screen for a few seconds, and the player must memorize their spelling and correctly type them.  <br><br>Players can create and modify their own set of words, and copy them to another disk to allow other players to participate.",
